token_lists.title: genies' melancholics
token_lists.description:
I love melancholy in art. 

I love the pain we can cleanse ourselves of through expression, love the restless brushstrokes passioned by angst, the faded colours showing a reality here but not really, the stillness of a photograph capturing a relentlessly moving world, the hunger of a pleading soul.

You who suffer with a sense of calm
you who paint pain with beauty. 
I see you.

token_lists.title: A Thousand Cuts - An Uchujin Photo Series
token_lists.description:
A collection of photos shot over the 10 years and 1 day I lived in Japan.
Many who have never lived in Japan and know it only through it's popular culture have a somewhat rose tinted view of the country.
This collection is my attempt to articulate the darker side of a place that no matter how I tried never felt like home.

All 1/1 Editions
